title: Władysławowo, Warmian-Masurian Voivodeship
content:
Władysławowo [vwadɨswaˈvɔvɔ] is a village in the administrative district of Gmina Elbląg, within Elbląg County, Warmian-Masurian Voivodeship, in northern Poland.[1] It lies approximately 9 kilometres (6 mi) north-west of Elbląg and 88 km (55 mi) north-west of the regional capital Olsztyn.
